raw_data.description: Monitors the performance of each task or group of tasks and informs project stakeholders of all accomplishments, issues, and resolutions. raw_data.title: Software Architect
raw_data.description: Provides highly technical and specialized guidance and solutions to complex problems. Leads technical requirement definition, analysis and design activities, and identifies appropriate technologies for desired solutions. Performs software design/architecture and software development, particularly prototyping complex solutions and applying new technologies. Documents the system architecture and design using industry best practices. Plans system integration phase and testing approaches. Collaborates with the project manager to determine scope and timelines. Responsible for ensuring that the implemented technical solution follows the planned architecture. Ensures these systems are compatible and in compliance with the standards for component based architecture, open systems architectures, and profiles of standards. Analyzes systematically problems of workflows, organization, and planning and develops appropriate corrective action. Provides daily supervision and direction to technical staff and interacts with other teams. Works closely with the project manager to define the software development methodology appropriate for the project. Follows industry trends and identifies new technological areas to prototype with and or apply. Has experience in multiple areas of software engineering, in-depth knowledge of the technology landscape, strong design and programming skills, excellent background in architecture, design and development of web-based systems on different technology platforms such as Java, .Net etc. Experience in analysis and design must include the use of UML. Uses frameworks, design patterns, implementation and test tools to support project goals. Capable of taking responsibility for the technology baseline for the project and using best practices for system development and delivering it on time within the budgetary constraints. Possess excellent writing and oral communication skills and ability to interact with the customer/client.
